Title : A child with muscle-eye-brain disease. Ophthalmological and neurological characteristics.
Date : 2001
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : To describe a child with Muscle-Eye-Brain disease (MEB), one of three types of congenital muscular dystrophy associated with ocular abnormalities.Case report.The child showed severe visual impairment due to progressive myopia and retinal degeneration, a pachygyria-type of migration disorder of the brain with a nodular cortical surface, i.e. cobblestone cortex, as well as muscular weakness and severe mental retardation.Ophthalmological assessments are important to help to diagnose and follow children with congenital muscular dystrophy.
